mplement the complete enemy progression system, Elite Shooter rules, spawn caps, player life, and difficulty alerts for the Canvas shoot ’em up game.

1️⃣ Player Life

Initial life: 5

Existing extra-life mechanics remain unchanged

2️⃣ Enemy Spawn Rate & Density
Rushers & Shooters

After 100 kills: spawn rate increases

After 300 kills: no more normal Rushers or Shooters

Spawn rules:

Shooters obey upper-half screen restriction

Rushers follow normal movement rules

Early Game Density Caps:

Kills < 5 → max 2 enemies on screen

Kills < 10 → max 5 enemies on screen

3️⃣ Elite Shooter Rules
Pre-100 Kills: Regular Elite Shooter

Spawn frequency: every 30 kills

Max on screen: 1

Behavior:

Random movement

Shooting modes: rapid-fire bullets + Rusher spawn

Rewards: power-up + extra life

HP scaling: based on player power levels

150–299 Kills: Regular Elite Shooter

Spawn frequency: every 30 kills

Max on screen: 3

Behavior: same as pre-100 rules

Rewards: power-up + extra life

Post-300 Kills: Dual Elite System
Type A — Replacement Elites

Spawn condition: replace Shooters

Behavior: move like normal Shooters (vertical from top or horizontal in upper half)

No random movement, no shooting modes, no Rushers

Rewards: none

Number on screen: unlimited

Type B — Original Elite Shooter

Spawn condition: every 30 kills (as pre-300 rules)

Behavior: random movement + shooting modes

Rewards: power-up + extra life

Number on screen: unlimited

4️⃣ Difficulty Alerts (On-Screen Messages)

After 100 kills:

Display large text at bottom: "The enemies are getting angrier!!!"

After 150 kills:

Display: "More angry Jelly are coming"

Post-300 kills:

Display: "Behold! Here is the real Angry Horde!"

Display style: large, prominent, temporary but noticeable, does not block gameplay


Design Constraints

Maintain modular logic for:

Type A vs Type B elites

Spawn frequency scaling

Max elite counts per stage

Alerts are non-blocking, rendered on bottom of canvas

Rushers spawned by Type B elites follow original rules

Player collision, power-up, and extra-life logic remain unchanged

Enemy density caps for early game (<10 kills) still enforced

Spawn positions respect upper-half screen restriction for horizontal spawns

