v0.2 ***********************************************************************
1️⃣ Entering Debug Mode

Activation:

Game is paused

Press Enter on keyboard

Debug mode toggles on/off

2️⃣ Debug Mode Features

On-screen indicator

Display text: "DEBUG MODE"

Position: top-right corner

Blinks or flashes to be noticeable

Player Invincibility

While debug mode is active: player cannot take damage

Blink / invincibility logic does not interfere

Manipulate Enemy Kill Count

While in debug mode:

Typing a number + Enter sets the current enemy kills to that value

This triggers enemy progression rules immediately (spawn rates, elite spawning, difficulty alerts, etc.)

3️⃣ Design Constraints

Debug mode cannot break existing gameplay loops

All changes are instant but reversible (toggle off to resume normal behavior)

Debug input only active while paused

Maintain all existing collision, power-ups, and elite rules

Visual debug text should not interfere with other UI elements

4️⃣ Output Requirements

Update only pause menu / input / debug logic

Briefly explain:

How debug mode toggling is implemented

How player invincibility is enforced

How number + Enter updates enemy kill count